[1.775, "o", "\u001b[1mcoop\u001b[0m v0.0.0-20260710100806-021411f78fda+dirty — run a coding agent all night long in a box it can't escape.\r\r\nUsage: coop <command> [args]\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mAGENTS\u001b[0m\r\r\n  coop <agent>[:model][@account]    a sandboxed agent (the target grammar)\r\r\n  coop fusion <gov> --peer <a>…     one leads, named peers advise\r\r\n  coop acp <agent|fusion>           serve as an editor agent (ACP; e.g. Zed)\r\r\n  coop <agent> --consult <peer>…    a read-only second opinion, named peers\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mCREDENTIALS, MODELS & PRESETS\u001b[0m\r\r\n  coop login <agent>                sign in an agent (a subscription)\r\r\n  coop credentials [agent]          stored credentials + which are signed in\r\r\n  coop models [agent]               the model menu per agent\r\r\n  coop presets [name]               orchestration recipes (lead + roles)\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mTHE BOX\u001b[0m\r\r\n  coop run -- <cmd...>              run a raw command in the box\r\r\n  coop shell                        an interactive shell in the box\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mFORKS — review and land work like a PR\u001b[0m\r\r\n  coop fork <name> [target]         open or re-enter a fork and run an agent\r\r\n  coop fork ls                      list this repo's forks\r\r\n  coop fork review <name>           show a fork's review dossier + diff\r\r\n  coop fork merge <name>            rebase the fork onto your branch and land it\r\r\n  coop fork logs [name]             tail a fork's loop log (no name: every fork)\r\r\n  coop fork rm <name>               discard a fork\r\r\n  coop fork stop <name>             stop a detached loop\r\r\n  coop fork open <name>             open the fork in your editor\r\r\n  coop fork path <name>             print the fork's filesystem path\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mUNATTENDED\u001b[0m\r\r\n  coop loop [agent]                 work the queue(s) until done, then review\r\r\n  coop fleet init                   write the .agent/fleet.yaml template\r\r\n  coop fleet up                     start every fork's loop, detached\r\r\n  coop fleet down                   stop the fleet's running loops\r\r\n  coop fleet watch                  live dashboard of every fork's progress\r\r\n  coop fleet prune                  drop forks no longer in the fleet file\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mTASKS — a folder-per-task queue in .agent/tasks/\u001b[0m\r\r\n  coop tasks ls                     show the queue, grouped by state\r\r\n  coop tasks watch                  live board of the queue + active forks\r\r\n  coop tasks add \"<title>\"          add a task (then claim/block/unblock/done)\r\r\n  coop tasks decisions              what's blocked on a decision (-i to answer)\r\r\n  coop backlog                      park unscheduled ideas; promote when ready\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mSERVICES — the box's compose.agent.yml sidecars\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[2mcoop up                           none in compose.agent.yml yet\u001b[0m\r\r\n  \u001b[2mcoop down                         stop the compose.agent.yml services\u001b[0m\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mSAFETY — prove the box holds, catch committed secrets\u001b[0m\r\r\n  coop doctor                       attack the box, prove isolation holds\r\r\n  coop check-secrets                scan the working tree for committed secrets\r\r\n\r\r\n\u001b[1mSETUP & MAINTENANCE\u001b[0m\r\r\n  coop init [--stack asdf]          scaffold the queue, hooks, skills, subagents\r\r\n  coop build                        build the box image (stable, pinned)\r\r\n  coop update                       self-update coop, then rebuild the box\r\r\n  coop completion <shell>           shell tab-completion (bash, zsh)\r\r\n  coop prompt                       a one-line status for a shell prompt / tmux\r\r\n  coop help                         this help\r\r\n  coop version                      print the version\r\r\n\r\r\nRun 'coop help <command>' or 'coop <command> --help' for a command's details —\r\r\nfor an agent (claude/codex/gemini), --help is the agent's own.\r\r\n\r\r\nConfig  ~/.config/coop/coop.conf, or COOP_* env vars\r\r\nAuth    ~/.config/coop/agents\r\r\nDocs    https://coop.dryga.com\r\r\n"]
